    "en": {
      "title": "An announcement from the Indian High Commission",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Indian High Commission in Sri Lanka has issued a statement saying that it strongly rejects the baseless and speculative media reports that India exerted pressure on Sri Lankan political leaders during the vote held in Parliament today (20) to elect the successor president of Sri Lanka.",
        "According to the statement, the Indian High Commission once again emphasizes that India will provide support at all times to achieve the aspirations of Sri Lankans in accordance with the democratic methods and values \u200b\u200bas well as the constitutional provisions through the established constitutional institutions.",
        "The Indian High Commission stated that India will never interfere in the internal affairs or democratic process of another country."
      ],
